The paper deals with the problem of efficient search for similar objects in high dimensional and sparse datasets, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science. The proposed compression scheme is based on techniques used in data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and databases (cs.DB).
